    java.lang.AutoCloseable
    public class ReadUpdateResultSet
extends ResultSet
    This class represents a direct read and exclusive document lock into the database, obtained as a result of a Connection.readOneForUpdate(String, String).

      • close

        public void close()
           throws java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                  EzNoSQLException
        Description copied from class: ResultSet
        Ends positioning into the EzNoSQL database previously obtained by the Connection.read(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) or Connection.readGeneric(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) ResultSet methods. Any resources associated with the ResultSet instance are freed, and for non-recoverable databases, any document level locks will be released. This method is invoked automatically on objects managed by the try-with-resources statement.
        Specified by:
        close in interface java.lang.AutoCloseable
        Overrides:
        close in class ResultSet
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If the Connection instance or resultToken field is invalid (i.e. already closed)
        EzNoSQLException - If the call returned an error, see class for detailed usage and error handling.
